{
  "texts": [
    "According to Rashid et al. (2022), quality feedback focused on detecting problems, providing suggestions or pointing out where changes needed to be made.",
    "They found students were likely to find a review helpful if a suggestion was provided along with the identified problem.",
    "Detection of problems in reviews was also pursued by Xiao et al. (2022).",
    "They tried several machine-learning and neural network models, finding that their proposed new algorithm was as or more efficient.",
    "Saccardi et al. (2023) designed a system for identifying students' group work problems which addressed feedback on teamwork, rather than feedback on an artifact produced by an individual or a team."
  ]
}